/model
# we select model by name or by index
# let's select qwen2.5-coder:14b (index 6)
/model set 6
# we check the model we selected
/model
# we list all available skills
/skill available
# we load a skill, javadoc.md file we pre-filled with some instructions
/skill load javadoc
# lets show what we have loaded so far
/context files
/context all 1-3
# now lets call the model with a targeted task
# note that, because we just started ollama, it will take a while to load the model...
as a senior architect, provide javadoc for /home/vpc/xprojects/nuts-world/nuts-productivity/naru/core/naru-api/src/main/java/net/thevpc/naru/api/agent/NaruAgent.java
# because we are in planning mode, changes to apply only shown not applied
# ────────────────────────────────────
# PHASE 4: Routines & Workflow"
# ────────────────────────────────────
# we start to check what we have as routines
#/routine list
# ensure the current routine name and content (should be empty)
/routine name
/routine
# we add some lines to the routine
20 Based on these files, describe what this project does in one sentence. do not call any tool.
10 /sys find . -name "*.java" 2>/dev/null | head -20
# lets check the routine
/routine
# finally lets run the routine
/routine run
# Note that you can create multiple routines...
# and add conditions and loops (using /if, /while, /for...)
# and even create sub-routines (functions), check the documentation for more details...

# ────────────────────────────────────
# PHASE 5: Flow Control Examples
# ────────────────────────────────────

# --- nested /for + /if : dispatch a different prompt per iteration ---
/for i : 1 .. 3
    /if i == 1
        List all public interfaces in this project.
    /elseif i == 2
        List all abstract classes in this project.
    /else
        List all concrete implementations in this project.
    /end
/end

# --- /while : refine iteratively until done ---
/set iteration = 1
/while iteration <= 3
    /set iteration = iteration + 1
    Refine the javadoc you generated, improve clarity and add @throws where missing.
/end

# lets exit
/exit
